{{pagebanner|Plantage banner Hortus botanicus.jpg|caption=East entrance bridge to the Hortus Botanicus|pgname=Plantage|origin=-0.4,0}} '''Plantage''' (''Plantation'' in [[Dutch phrasebook|Dutch]]) is a leafy neighbourhood in the centre of [[Amsterdam]]. This article also covers the '''Eastern Islands'''.
==Understand== {{Mapframe|52.36833|4.91739|zoom=14}} {{Mapshapes|Q2060132|stroke-width=2.5}} {{Mapshapes|Q260870}} {{Mapmask |52.3658,4.9012 |52.3592,4.9047 |52.3597,4.9067 |52.3606,4.9083 |52.3605,4.9102 |52.3612,4.9118 |52.3622,4.9183 |52.3632,4.9199 |52.3637,4.9223 |52.3665,4.9272 |52.3666,4.9319 |52.3688,4.9328 |52.3700,4.9330 |52.3718,4.9325 |52.3732,4.9305 |52.3752,4.9236 |52.3768,4.9131 |52.3751,4.9128 |52.3714,4.9133 |52.3667,4.9061}}
==Get in==
===By tram=== [[File:AmsterdamTram.svg|thumbnail|right|Amsterdam tram & metro system]] As walking to Plantage can take more than 20 minutes, most visitors would take the tram to get there. {{marker| type=go | name=Tram {{rint|amsterdam|7}} | alt=Slotermeer to Azartplein | url=https://reisinfo.gvb.nl/en/travel-information/line/GVB/7 | email= | address= | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2025-11-25 }} from Leidseplein heads northeast through the district via Alexanderplein. Tram stops Hoogte Kadijk and 1e Coehoornstraat are near the windmill De Gooyer. It also connects with the metro at '''Weesperplein''' metro station. {{marker|type=go | name=Tram {{rint|amsterdam|14}} | alt=Amsterdam Centraal to Javaplein | url=https://reisinfo.gvb.nl/en/travel-information/line/GVB/14 | email= | address= | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2025-11-25 }} from Amsterdam Centraal passes through the district with stops at Artis, Plantage Lepellaan and Alexanderplein. It also connects with the metro at '''Waterlooplein''' metro station.
===By metro===
The metro is the fastest way to get into the district, but the locations of its stops are somewhat less convenient than the tram stops. Two stations serve the Plantage. '''Waterlooplein''' is the closest to the main sights, including the Artis Zoo, the various museums and the Hollandsche Schouwburg. Exiting the station at ''Hortusplantsoen'', it's only a short walk to the area. '''Weesperplein''' is close to the University of Amsterdam and the Carré Theatre. Three metro lines from Centraal Station (lines '''51''', '''53''' and '''54''') stop at both stations.
==See== [[File:De Gooyer Windmill.jpg|300px|thumbnail|De Gooyer]] The Plantage Amsterdam is a green area, mostly known for Artis Zoo and the Hortus, the botanical garden. In fact, most of Amsterdam's museums are gathered in this area. Just beyond the Waterlooplein, you will find — amongst many other museums — the historical buildings of The Jewish Cultural Quarter, the renowned Hermitage Museum and the impressive Scheepvaartmuseum.
<!--do not add Magere Brug here. It's already in [[Amsterdam/Canal District]].--> * {{see | name=Natura Artis Magistra Zoo | alt=Artis | url=https://www.artis.nl/nl/language/visitors-information/ | email=info@artis.nl | address=Plantage Kerklaan 38-40 | lat=52.366205 | long=4.915954 | directions= | phone=+31 20 523 34 00 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Youth (3 to 9 years) €18, adult (10 to 64 years) €21.50, seniors (65 +) €17.50 | wikipedia=Natura Artis Magistra | image=NL-Artis-ingang.jpg | wikidata=Q713124 | lastedit=2017-07-03 | content=An entry ticket for Artis also provides admission to the Planetarium, the Aquarium and the Zoological Museum. Artis is also a botanical garden, with plants and trees gathered from all over the world, just like the animal species. Don't miss the [http://www.artis.nl/nl/te-doen-artis/dagagenda-activiteiten/zoomeravonden/ Artis ZOOmeravonden]. }} * {{see | name=Hortus Botanicus | alt= | url=http://dehortus.nl | email= | address=Plantage Middenlaan 2 | lat=52.366969 | long=4.908442 | directions=Tram Mr. Visserplein | phone=+31 20 625 90 21 | tollfree= | hours=10:00-17:00 | price=Adult €9.75; seniors and children €5.50 | wikipedia=Hortus Botanicus (Amsterdam) | image=The Hortus Botanicus Amsterdam entrance Photo by Pejman Akbarzadeh Persian Dutch Network.jpg | wikidata=Q1576733 | lastedit=2016-06-12 | content=The Amsterdam Botanical Gardens — 'Hortus' as they are called by locals — used to be the Botanic Garden of the University of Amsterdam. It is one of the oldest botanical gardens in the world. Nowadays it is an independent organisation. The collection of the garden consists of more than 6,000 species. The garden regularly holds extra exhibitions and music performances. }} * {{see | name=Wertheimpark | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=52.368056 | long=4.909167 | directions=opposite the Hortus Botanicus | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikipedia=nl:Wertheimpark | image=Wertheimpark.jpg | wikidata=Q3149634 | content=A small park with a World War II memorial located at one of the nicest canals in Amsterdam. }} * {{see | name=H'ART | alt= | url=https://www.hartmuseum.nl/en/ | email= | address=Amstel 51 | lat=52.365 | long=4.9025 | directions=Metro Waterlooplein | phone=+31 20 530 8755 | tollfree= | hours=Daily 10:00-17:00 | price=Standard (adults and children aged 18 or over) €22.50, children up to 17 years old free | wikidata=Q1350009 | lastedit=2025-02-18 | content=Founded as an outpost of the Hermitage in St Petersburg, ties were severed with the parent institution following Russia's war in Ukraine. After a hasty rebrand, the H'ART museum reopened in April 2022 with a focus on Dutch heritage in Amsterdam. }} * {{see | name=Scheepvaartmuseum | alt= | url=http://www.hetscheepvaartmuseum.nl/ | email= | address=Kattenburgerplein 1 | lat=52.371389 | long=4.914722 | directions= | phone=+31 20 523-2222 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=09:00-17:00 daily | price=€15 adults; €7.50 children, students and seniors (prices 2014) | wikipedia=Nederlands Scheepvaartmuseum | image=Amsterdam - Nederlands Scheepvaartmuseum 18.JPG | wikidata=Q1616123 | content=Het Scheepvaartmuseum reopened in late 2011 following major renovations. Stimulating, interactive exhibitions allow visitors to explore 500 years of maritime history. The building, called the Arsenal, is impressive. The Central Square, the indoor courtyard can be visited for free and takes your breath away. Also the museum shop, the restaurant and the library are open to the public free of charge. }} * {{see | name=Verzetsmuseum | alt=Dutch Resistance Museum | url=http://www.verzetsmuseum.org/museum/en/museum | email=info@verzetsmuseum.org | address=Plantage Kerklaan 61D | lat=52.3677 | long=4.91274 | directions=Tram 14 to Artis | phone=+31 20 620 25 35 | tollfree= | hours=M-F 10:00-17:00, Sa Su 11:00-17:00 | price=Adult €12.00, ages 7-17 €6.50 | wikipedia=Verzetsmuseum | image=Gebouw Plancius.jpg | wikidata=Q828307 | lastedit=2020-10-30 | content=Museum showing what Amsterdam and Holland were like during Nazi occupation. Has a very nice children's section. If you are visiting with kids and want to go to a museum about the Second World War in the Netherlands this is definitely recommended. }} * {{see | name=De Gooyer | alt= | url= | email= | address=Funenkade 7 | lat=52.366667 | long=4.926111 | directions=Tram 7 to Hoogte Kadijk, bus 22 to Oostenburgergracht | phone= | tollfree= | hours=W-Su 15:00-19:00 | price= | wikipedia=De Gooyer, Amsterdam | image=De gooyer amsterdam.jpg | wikidata=Q2756543 | content=It's the only windmill (1814, restored) in the centre of Amsterdam, and the closest one that's open to visitors. }} * {{see | name=Micropia | alt= | url=https://www.micropia.nl/en | email= | address=Plantage Kerklaan 38-40 | lat=52.36697 | long=4.91274 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours=11:00-17:00 | price=Age 10 and up €16, ages 3-9 €14 | wikidata=Q18169481 | lastedit=2020-10-26 | content=Museum about microbes. }}
