* {{sleep | name=Bilderberg Garden Hotel | alt= | url=http://www.bilderberg.nl/uk/hotels/gardenhotel/ | email=garden.reservation@bilderberg.nl | address=Dijsselhofplantsoen 7 | lat=52.35111 | long=4.87412 | directions= | phone=+31 20 - 570 56 00 | tollfree= | fax=+31 20 - 570 56 54 | checkin= | checkout= | price= | content=Five-star hotel just off the Apollolaan. }} * {{sleep | name=Hilton Amsterdam | alt= | url=https://www.hilton.com/en/hotels/amshitw-hilton-amsterdam/ | email=info.amsterdam@hilton.com | address=Apollolaan 138 | lat=52.35153 | long=4.87207 | directions=in Oud-Zuid | phone=+31 20 710 60 00 | tollfree= | checkin=15:00 | checkout=12:00 | price=From €200 | content=Internationally famous as the site of John Lennon's and Yoko Ono's bed-in. Nationally famous for being where Dutch artist Herman Brood killed himself. }} * {{sleep | name=Hotel Okura | url=http://www.okura.nl | email= | address=Ferdinand Bolstraat 333 | lat=52.348714 | long=4.893862 | directions= | phone=+31 20 6788 300 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=€275 | checkin= | checkout= | content=Five-star Japanese-owned and -operated hotel with an excellent range of Japanese food, clothing, and book shops in the basement, and wireless internet in the lobby, bar, and conference rooms. The only drawback is that it's relatively distant from the central station (15 minutes by tram), but worth considering if work is paying and you don't mind taking cabs. }} * {{sleep | name=Park Hotel Amsterdam | url=http://www.parkhotel.nl | email= | address=Stadhouderskade 25 | lat=52.361421 | long=4.883174 | directions= | phone=+31 20 671 12 22 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=From €149 | checkin= | checkout= | content=Bang in the middle of Amsterdam between Leidseplein, Rijksmuseum and P.C. Hooftstraat. Four-star hotel spread over several historical buildings. Parking. Very friendly staff. }} * {{sleep | name=Conservatorium Hotel | url=http://www.conservatoriumhotelamsterdam.com/ | email= | address=Van Baerlestraat 27 | lat=52.358631 | long=4.878624 | directions= | phone=+31 20 570 00 00 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content=Five-star hotel offers 129 guest suites spread throughout 8 floors. }} * {{sleep | name=Hotel JL No76 | alt= | url=http://hoteljlno76.com | email=info@hoteljlno76.com | address=Jan Luijkenstraat 76 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+31 20 3485 555 | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2016-09-01 | content=Hotel JL No76 is a luxury boutique hotel 2½ blocks from Vondelpark. }}
==Connect==
The '''Rijksmuseum''' and '''Van Gogh Museum''' have free Wi-Fi throughout the museum, and the '''Stedelijk Museum''' has Wi-Fi and laptop connections available in the reading room of its library. '''Bagels & Beans''' branches also offer unlimited free Wi-Fi access, and can be found in the Ferdinand Bolstraat (near the Albert Cuyp Market and Heinekenplein), Van Baerlestraat (near the P.C. Hooftstraat and Vondelpark) and the Pernassusweg (near the Zuidas).
==Go next==
If you haven't had enough of the museums, go to the '''Hermitage''' in [[Amsterdam/Plantage|Plantage]] and the '''Anne Frank House''' in the [[Amsterdam/Canal District|Canal District]]. The Canal District also has some quality dining and shopping options.
If you want to go completely off the beaten track, visit the urban forest '''Amsterdamse Bos''' in [[Amstelveen]]. It's three times the size of New York's Central Park and is visited by 4.5 million visitors annually (mostly locals). You can take a walk, hire a bicycle or go rowing or riding. If you're with children, visit the pancake restaurant or the petting zoo.
