==Do==
==Buy== * {{buy | name=Ten Katemarkt | alt= | url=http://tenkatemarkt.nl | email= | address=Ten Katestraat 97-99 | lat=52.366868 | long=4.866848 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M-Sa 08:00-17:00 | price= | image=Amsterdam-TenKatestraatMarkt-20081229.jpg | content=Third largest in Amsterdam with food, households, flowers and clothing. }}
==Eat== * {{eat | name=Dosa | alt= | url=https://www.dosarestaurant.nl/ | email= | address=Overtoom 146 | lat=52.362458 | long=4.873326 | directions=Vondelpark | phone=+31 20 6164 838 | tollfree= | hours= | price=€16+ per main | lastedit=2023-08-27 | content=They specialise in traditional Southern Indian cuisine, especially the eponymous 'Dosa' (a rice and lentil pancake with a variety of fillings). The food is outstanding and well worth hunting out. The dosas are exceptional and a treat worthy of a visit by themselves. }} * {{eat | name=Foodhallen | alt= | url=https://www.foodhallen.nl/venues/amsterdam | email= | address=Bellamyplein 51 | lat=52.3671 | long=4.8681 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours=Su-Th 12:00-23:00, F Sa 12:00-00:00 | price=€10+ | lastedit=2023-08-27 | content=International food court with 20 food-stands housed in a large building that was once a tram depot. }} * {{eat | name=Hap Hmm | alt= | url=https://www.hap-hmm.nl/ | email= | address=Eerste Helmersstraat 33, 1054 CZ, Amsterdam | lat=52.36371 | long=4.87645 | directions= | phone=+312 07708924 | tollfree= | hours=M-F 17:00-21:15, closed Sa Su | price=€12+ mains | lastedit=2023-08-27 | content=Traditional Dutch cuisine. The restaurant may be cramped, but it does serve some quality and rustic Dutch fare. This place is cash only. }} * {{eat | name=Sora Sapporo Ramen - West | alt= | url=https://ramensora.nl/ | email= | address=Marco Polostraat 223H | lat=52.37113 | long=4.85513 | directions=just off the Marco Polostratt tram & bus stop | phone=+31 202390780 | tollfree= | hours=M-F 12:30-15:00, 17:00-21:00; Sa Su 12:00-21:00 | price=€16+ | lastedit=2023-08-27 | content=Small ramen restaurant with friendly staff, quick service, and good selection of ramen & appetizers. Also serve beer & sake. Closes early and small seating so might want to reserve on weekends. }}
==Drink==
* {{drink | name=TonTon Club West | alt= | url=https://tontonclub.nl/ | email=reserveren@tontonclub.nl | address=Polonceaukade 27 | lat=52.38601 | long=4.86605 | directions=Bus Van Hallstraat | phone=+31 6 13300314 | tollfree= | hours=Daily 13:00-01:00 | price=€15+ per main, €1 per game | lastedit=2023-08-27 | content=TonTon Club is an excellent place for a good night out. The place has a unique atmosphere with Japan as its inspiration. Upstairs there are arcades and button bashers, downstairs there's room for drinks and board games. You can also order Japanese snacks. Be early as tables are often reserved. }} * {{drink | name=Cafe L'Affice | alt= | url=http://www.cafelaffiche.nl/ | email= | address=Jacob van Lennepstraat 39 | lat=52.36658 | long=4.87475 | directions= | phone=+31 2 06121959 | tollfree= | hours=F Sa 11:30-01:00, Su-Th 11:30-00:30 | price= | lastedit=2022-06-01 | content=Small bar with friendly staff and a cosy and candle-lit atmosphere. Selection of beers on tap and in bottles, including a triple blonde specially made for the bar. Small selection of bar food as well. }} ===Nightclubs===
* {{drink | name=Club 8 | alt= | url=https://club-8.nl/ | email= | address=Admiraal de Ruijterweg 56b | lat=52.371253 | long=4.859715 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | content=A large alternative place with lots of art on its walls. There's ping pong, a very local and fairly young crowd. }}
==Sleep== === Budget === * {{sleep | name=Hotel ABBA | alt= | url=http://www.hotel-abba.nl/ | email= | address=Overtoom 118-122 | lat=52.362765 | long=4.874552 | directions=Vondelpark, Tram: Overtoom or Eerste Constantijn Huygensstraat | phone=+31 20 618 3058 | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | content=Cheap but clean hotel, close to the Van Gogh and Rijksmuseum. }} * {{sleep | name=MissOrtelia | alt=Baarjes | url=http://www.missortelia.com | email=info@missortelia.com | address=Orteliuskade 51-I | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+31 616 111 349 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=€40/90 | checkin=flexible | checkout=10:30. Free luggage store | content=Free bikes - Wi-fi free - breakfast included. }} * {{sleep | name=Holiday Inn Express Amsterdam - Sloterdijk Station | alt= | url= | email= | address= Zaventemweg 3 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2015-03-23 | content=This HIExpress is right in the midst of the web of tracks extending around Sloterdijk station, making it very convenient for travel to just about any point in Amsterdam. That said, the actual area around the hotel is a sombre office park and a huge "transferium", so it is best to only come there to sleep and have (free) breakfast. }} * {{sleep | name=Meininger Hotel Amsterdam City West | alt= | url= | email= | address=Orlyplein 1-67 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price=€41 | lastedit=2015-03-23 | content=The Meininger chain's properties sit somewhere between budget hotels and hostels, with available multi-person rooms with bunk beds and on-site laundrette. The hotel is relatively new and visually attractive if rather basic inside. Again, staying in the midst of Sloterdijk is great for transit possibilities and rather unexciting regarding everything else. }} * {{sleep | name=Stayokay Vondelpark | url=http://www.stayokay.com/vondelpark | email=vondelpark@stayokay.com | address=Zandpad 5 | lat=52.361146 | long=4.878186 | directions=Tram Stadhouderskade | phone=+31 20 589 8996 | tollfree= | fax=+31 20 589 8955 | hours= | price=Dorms from €17, privates from €50 | checkin=early check-in begins at 07:30, rooms available at 14:00 | checkout=10:30 | content=Fairly large youth hostel, very clean and professional, operated by the Dutch affiliate of Hostelling International. Next to the pleasant Vondelpark, puts you on the south-western side of the city center and just a few blocks from the Van Gogh Museum and the Rijksmuseum. The breakfast is filling and has a social atmosphere. This location is popular with school groups. Bring a padlock for your locker, or purchase one at the desk. }}
=== Mid-range === * {{sleep | name=Bastion Hotel Amsterdam Zuidwest |alt=| url=https://www.bastionhotels.com/nl-nl/hotels/hotel-amsterdam-zuidwest | email= | address=Nachtwachtlaan 11 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+31 20 669 1621 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= |lastedit=2019-01-24| content= }} * {{sleep | name=Ramada Apollo Amsterdam Centre | alt= | url= | email= | address=Staalmeesterslaan 410 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2015-03-23 | content=The Ramada is a solid property, but calling it "Amsterdam Centre" was not even close to reality, as the hotel is at the remote end of Rembrandtpark, close to the A10 ring road running across Amsterdam-West. That said, you will find getting to the city quite easy thanks to them tram 13 stop at the hotel's back and the park provides a tranquil environment. The best rooms have great views of Amsterdam over the park; the less fortunate guests will have to enjoy residential blocks of Slotervaart. The good news is that the hotel has a top-floor restaurant, bar and terrace for everybody to enjoy the best views. }} * {{sleep | name=Roemer Hotel | alt= | url=http://www.hotelroemer.com/en | email= | address=Roemer Visscherstraat 10 | lat=52.361774 | long=4.877998 | directions= | phone=+31 20 612 01 20 | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price=Doubles from €129 | content=Trendy boutique hotel. }} * {{sleep | name=Hotel Espresso City Center | alt= | url=https://www.hotelespresso.nl/ | email= | address=Overtoom 57 | lat=52.3629 | long=4.8764 | directions=at Eerste Constantijn Huygensstraat | phone=+31 20 412 0880 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | lastedit=2021-11-07 | content=Near Leidseplein with tram connections and bus to airport. Near Vondelpark and Museumplein. Buffet breakfast available at extra cost. Unlimited free coffee (including koffie verkeerd, the Dutch equivalent of café au lait) for guests in the lobby area. }}
=== Splurge === * {{sleep | name=Amsterdam Marriott Hotel | alt= | url=https://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/amsnt-amsterdam-marriott-hotel/ | email= | address=Stadhouderskade 12 | lat=52.362557 | long=4.880102 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2015-03-23 | content=At the border of ''Oud-West'' and the [[Amsterdam/Canal District|Canal District]], this old-fashioned Marriott can offer a relatively attractive rate and still has a convenient location for exploring the city centre. }} * {{sleep | name=Park Plaza Amsterdam Airport | url=http://www.parkplaza.com/hotels/netairp | email=ppaares@pphe.com | address=Melbournestraat 1, Lijnden | lat=52.348587 | long=4.765281 | directions= | phone=+31 20 6580 580 | tollfree= | fax=+31 20 6580 585 | hours= | price=From €79 | checkin= | checkout= | content=The hotel has 19 meeting rooms as well as 6 business suites. The hotel provides free shuttle service from and to the airport as well as free wi-fi in public areas. }}
